  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MECHANISMS DEVELOPED FOR CONTINUOUS MONITORING</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The target is to establish baseline and M&amp;E framework; develop and operationalise online monitoring system established; recruit and train 50 participatory stewards for programme implementation. 

The baseline study, cluster development report and M&amp;E framework was completed. The programme identified 22 bamboo clusters (Ethiopia6, Kenya8, and Uganda8) and mobilised 10675 households (Ethiopia3650, Kenya3475, and Uganda:3550) for interventions. The development of online geographical project monitoring and evaluation system is in progress and is expected to be completed by mid of 2021. The programme deployed 12 participatory stewards(PS) in different clusters for extension support and community mobilization and field data collection.</narrative>
  </description>
